    "body": "Consider the following code in python 2.7:\r\n\r\n```python\r\n#!/usr/bin/env python\r\ndef f():\r\n    for i in range(3):\r\n        if i < 4:\r\n            continue\r\n        has_more = False\r\n    return has_more\r\n```\r\n\r\nOnce compiled to `tmp.so`:\r\n\r\n```\r\n>>> from tmp import f\r\n>>> f()\r\nFalse\r\n```\r\n\r\nExpected output (that the python file results in):\r\n```\r\n>>> from tmp import f\r\n>>> f()\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"<stdin>\", line 1, in <module>\r\n  File \"tmp.py\", line 9, in f\r\n    return has_more\r\nUnboundLocalError: local variable 'has_more' referenced before assignment\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
